.TH pnmmargin 1 "9 January 1991"
.IX pnmmargin
.SH NAME
pnmmargin - add a border to a portable anymap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pnmmargin
.RB [ -white | -black | -color
.IR colorspec ]
.I size
.RI [ pnmfile ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads a portable anymap as input.
Adds a border of the specified number of pixels,
and produces a portable anymap as output.
.IX margin
.IX border
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
You can specify the border color with the
.BR -white ,
.BR -black ,
and
.B -color
flags.  If no color is specified, the program makes a guess.
.PP
.SH "SEE ALSO"
pnm(5)
.SH BUGS
It's a script.
Scripts are not portable to non-Unix environments.
